    <axiom component="lesson-plan">
        <title>Differentiation</title>
        <p xml:id="auto_dvi1l2a4">
            <alert>Struggling Learners:</alert>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="auto_lvke3947">
            <ul>
                <li xml:id="auto_073hm8t4">
                    <p xml:id="auto_9qbt124j">Provide pre-made cone models with labelled dimensions.</p>
                </li>
                <li xml:id="auto_tsk7kbg6">
                    <p xml:id="auto_ehcfb1vt">Use cones with simple whole-number dimensions for initial practice.</p>
                </li>
                <li xml:id="auto_1hgi67nu">
                    <p xml:id="auto_35yaty7z">Pair struggling learners with confident problem solvers.</p>
                </li>
                <li xml:id="auto_88ed2u2j">
                    <p xml:id="auto_oz7isnry">Break down the formula into steps: (1) Find base area <m>\pi r^2</m>, (2) Multiply by height, (3) Divide by 3.</p>
                </li>
                <li xml:id="auto_dr3knijc">
                    <p xml:id="auto_ix442vzd">Provide a step-by-step calculation template.</p>
                </li>
            </ul>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="auto_347h6cua">
            <alert>On-Level Learners:</alert>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="auto_aiijkt10">
            <ul>
                <li xml:id="auto_bqcwfrf3">
                    <p xml:id="auto_mb30ntdz">Verify the formula with the water pouring activity.</p>
                </li>
                <li xml:id="auto_bcykpo4v">
                    <p xml:id="auto_fgafo1kg">Explain the relationship between cones and cylinders to a peer.</p>
                </li>
                <li xml:id="auto_kx59ouio">
                    <p xml:id="auto_ke7anuru">Provide mixed practice with different dimensions, including problems where diameter is given instead of radius.</p>
                </li>
            </ul>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="auto_fg365xjg">
            <alert>Advanced Learners:</alert>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="auto_cjg8xrnl">
            <ul>
                <li xml:id="auto_m25w7oq9">
                    <p xml:id="auto_mb9ek178">Derive the formula using the relationship with cylinders.</p>
                </li>
                <li xml:id="auto_cv38o5hx">
                    <p xml:id="auto_7eqpsedx">Explore real-world applications: ice cream cones, funnels, traffic cones, conical tents.</p>
                </li>
                <li xml:id="auto_zx5v8nem">
                    <p xml:id="auto_mcrkhbow">Apply the concept to hollow cones (outer radius minus inner radius).</p>
                </li>
                <li xml:id="auto_92c4h1ov">
                    <p xml:id="auto_selhooig">Solve optimisation problems: Given a fixed volume, what dimensions minimise the surface area?</p>
                </li>
            </ul>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="auto_dbaoznvb">
            <alert>Extension Activity — Cone-Shaped Funnel Investigation:</alert>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="auto_8xuzh5q9">
            Work in groups.
        </p>
        <p xml:id="auto_igbxooxz">
            <ol markers="1.">
                <li xml:id="auto_b0pj7kuf">
                    <p xml:id="auto_cb0c35zt">Choose a real-world purpose for a cone-shaped funnel (e.g., pouring water, transferring grain, filtering liquids).</p>
                </li>
                <li xml:id="auto_5n4pwek2">
                    <p xml:id="auto_ff25sb25">Decide on the dimensions: radius and height.</p>
                </li>
                <li xml:id="auto_81108533">
                    <p xml:id="auto_a0x9irob">Calculate the volume of your funnel using the cone formula.</p>
                </li>
                <li xml:id="auto_cpcrsu6x">
                    <p xml:id="auto_ldfbvq32">If the funnel needs to hold <m>500 \; \text{cm}^3</m> of liquid, what dimensions would work?</p>
                </li>
                <li xml:id="auto_iqsatp52">
                    <p xml:id="auto_a63wvufm">Compare different funnel designs: tall and narrow vs. short and wide.</p>
                </li>
                <li xml:id="auto_7dlwih0t">
                    <p xml:id="auto_kapc4mz3">Present your findings with diagrams, measurements, and calculations.</p>
                </li>
            </ol>
        </p>
    </axiom>

